    • enableMap

      public void enableMap​(String featureValueName)
      Enable a feature values map for the given feature value name. When enabled, a map for featureValueName will be returned by getFeatureValuesMap(String).

      If a standard feature values name (like 'annotation' or 'stylistic') is enabled, this method has no effect. The method can be used to enable, for example, historical-forms.

      Specified by:
      enableMap in interface CSSFontFeatureValuesRule
      Parameters:
      featureValueName - the feature value name to be enabled.

    • getFeatureValuesMap

      Specified by:
      getFeatureValuesMap in interface CSSFontFeatureValuesRule
      Parameters:
      featureValueName - the feature value name.
      Returns:
      the feature values map, or null if the feature value name is not standard and has not been enabled by enableMap(String).

    • getTrailingComments

      public List<String> getTrailingComments()
      Description copied from class: AbstractCSSRule
      Get a list of the comments that immediately follow this rule, if any.

      If the parsing mode was COMMENTS_PRECEDING, or was COMMENTS_AUTO and the next comment happens after a newline character, it shall be assigned to the next rule as a preceding comment.
